description:
A DRM free digital series offered to readers at whatever price they would like to pay, and is planned to be a limited series of 10 issues; written by Brian K. Vaughan (Saga, Y: The Last Man, Ex Machina), illustrated by Marcos Martin (Fearless Defenders, Nova, Daredevil), and colored by Muntsa Vicente (Daredevil, Fear Itself: The Worthy). The comic book is self-published via www.panelsyndicate.com and available in English, Spanish, and Catalan.

The Private Eye is a detective story set in 2076, when everyone in the United States has a secret identity. Our protagonist is a member of the paparazzi, outlaw private investigators who dig up the kind of personal dirt no longer readily available through search engines. It’s a mystery with lots of masks, but no superpowers.

Awards:

  • 2015 Eisner Award for Best Digital/Web Comic
  • 2015 Harvey Award for Best Online Comics Work

Making-of Special:

  • The Private Eye: An Inside Look At the Creation of the Digital Comic #1

Collected Editions:

  • The Private Eye Volume One (Digital trade collecting issues #1-5 and material from An Inside Look.)
  • The Private Eye Volume Two (Digital trade collecting issues #6-10 and material from An Inside Look.)
  • The Private Eye: The Cloudburst Edition (Deluxe hardcover in widescreen format collecting issues #1-10 and material from An Inside Look; published by Image Comics.)
name: The Private Eye

description:
Five Ghosts: The Haunting of Fabian Gray was originally a five-issue mini-series written by Frank J. Barbiere and illustrated by Chris Mooneyham. Five Ghosts is a pulp adventure comic that started as a Kickstarter Project. The self-published comic proved successful and was picked up by Image Comics. Due to it's popularity, Image turned it into an Ongoing series with issue #6 in October 2013.

Plot Summary:

After a tragic encounter with an artifact known as "the dreamstone", infamous treasure hunter Fabian Gray was possessed by five literary ghosts (the wizard, the archer, the detective, the samurai, and the vampire) and has been granted access to their unique abilities. Of course, these powers have also come with a price.

Collected Editions

  • Five Ghosts: The Haunting of Fabian Gray (#1-5)
  • Five Ghosts: The Deluxe Edition Volume One (#1-12)
  • Five Ghosts: Lost Coastlines (#6-12)
  • Five Ghosts: Monsters & Men (#13-17)
name: Five Ghosts
